gsonpath

Annotation Type GsonPathDefaultConfiguration


  • @Retention(value=SOURCE)
@Target(value=TYPE)
public @interface GsonPathDefaultConfiguration
    Specifies a set of default values for the AutoGsonAdapter class.

    This can aid removing repetition for developers who are not happy with the defaults provided out of the box.

    To use this class correctly, you must annotate a class, and then whenever you which to use these defaults you must set the AutoGsonAdapter.defaultConfiguration() value to point to this annotated class.

    For example, creating defaults as follows: 

     @GsonPathDefaultConfiguration(flattenDelimiter = '$')
 class GsonPathDefaultConfiguration
 {
 }
    and then using it later: 
     @AutoGsonAdapter(defaults = GsonPathDefaultConfiguration.class)
 class ExampleModel
 {
 }
